text: Tarlo is a locality in the Southern Tablelands of New South Wales, Australia in Upper Lachlan Shire. It is located south of the township of Taralga, on the road to Goulburn. The Tarlo River and Tarlo River National Park and Cookbundoon Nature Reserve are located within the suburb of Tarlo. At the , it had a population of 164. == References == Category:Towns in New South Wales Category:Southern Tablelands Category:Upper Lachlan Shire Category:Goulburn Mulwaree Council
